news.title: China's Guangzhou R&F co-chief accused of bribery in U.S., London court hears
news.para: Zhang Li, who co-founded Hong Kong-listed R&F, is wanted on a provisional warrant issued in the Northern District of California that accuses him of participating in a scheme to bribe public officials between 2015 and 2020.

news.title: Bullish on India, to add Rs 2,500-crore projects in one year, says Trump Jr
news.para: The Trump Organisation will be ramping up its portfolio here through its India partner Tribeca Developers, which itself is looking to add projects worth Rs 5,000 crore, including its Trump branded portfolio, in 2023.

news.title: WeWork India expects to clock revenue of Rs 1,500 crore in FY23: CEO
news.para: The firm clocked 250% growth in earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortisation (EBIDTA) registering Rs 175 crore profit in 2022, as against a loss of Rs 120 crore last calendar year.

news.title: All residential & commercial properties to get unique digital door number in Jammu
news.para: The mapping of the residential and commercial properties would enable the citizens to avail maximum benefits of civic services as well as governance, the official said.

news.title: TARC prepays Rs 66 crore towards non-convertible debentures
news.para: BAIN Capital USA has invested by way of non-convertible debentures (NCDs) Rs 1,330 crore on April 29, 2022.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board gives Rs 23 crore to JMC-Greater for development work
news.para: ​This is for the first time in 15 years that the housing board gave 15% of its earnings to JMC-Greater, as stated in the provisions. The amount paid is for the financial year 2010-11 till 2021-22.

news.title: Master plan of three more cities up for government approval in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: The three cities where fresh focus has been made on spatial planning, public health facilities, water supply, urban transportation and socio-economic development through the master plan 2031 are Kanpur, Azamgarh and Hapur.

news.title: Nagpur development body's layouts to get provisional nod soon after applications
news.para: NMRDA commissioner Manoj Kumar Suryawanshi has also decided to send a copy of part of development plan (DP) to applicants through speed post. It will prevent people from travelling to NMRDA offices from rural parts of the district.

news.title: Pay to park outside houses: New plan to kick off from Chandigarh sector 35 D
news.para: Under it, parking space will be provided at the portion between the road and the boundary wall of houses. The space has been encroached upon by residents at many places.

news.title: Mumbai: Panel revived for decision on Dharavi redevelopment
news.para: According to a GR issued by the housing department, the CoS was constituted nearly 14 years ago and with the need for a speedy implementation of the project, it is being reconstituted.

news.title: Builders request Rajasthan government to remove double taxation in real estate deals
news.para: Credai-Rajasthan president Dhirendra Madan said, “The stamp duty and registration fees are charged twice for the same land which creates unnecessary burden on the buyer and investor.”

news.title: Structural audit in Gurugram: Basements of most buildings have flaws, more tests needed
news.para: DC Nishant Yadav held a meeting with the audit agencies along with representatives of RWAs and developers and department of town and country planning (DTCP) officials on Monday to discuss the report.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh police seeks extradition of Shine City owner from Dubai
news.para: Naseem, the owner of Shine City – a real estate firm, had duped investors of an estimated over Rs 350 crore by promising them flats, plots and houses which never came into being.

news.title: UK lenders see 23% slide in mortgages for home-buyers in 2023
news.para: Trade body UK Finance forecast on Monday that gross mortgage lending for house purchase would fall to 131 billion pounds ($161 billion) in 2023 from 171 billion pounds this year and a peak of 189 billion pounds in 2021, when pandemic-related tax incentives were in force.

news.title: TVS Capital's chairman buys Bengaluru residential property for Rs 15 crore
news.para: The property located at Rest House Crescent Road is spread over 6000 sq ft with 2600 sq ft built-up area. It includes a dwelling house, ouhouses, garage and other construction.
